 for bestpractices and # Listing Detail & Auction Page

## Overview
Build a comprehensive Listing Detail & Auction Page ecosystem for a high-concurrency, B2B physical asset auction platform. This task delivers a rich, detail-first listing view with full specs, media gallery, AI QA report, auction scheduling, bid history, and strong CTAs to join live bidding or place proxy bids. It integrates with a scalable search & filter experience, robust notifications (email, SMS, in-app), caching strategies for UI and backend performance, and a real-time Live Auction Room. The system emphasizes correctness, concurrency safety, modularity, and a reuse-first architecture that can swap AI/vision providers, while ensuring strict runtime safety rules for array handling and API responses.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Listing Detail & Auction Page is the primary, immersive view for a single asset/listing. It presents every facet needed to evaluate, bid, and participate in the auction: high-res media gallery, full specifications, AI QA report (structured JSON with highlights and evidence), an auction schedule (start time, batch windows, reserve status), bid history (anonymized buyers), and clear CTAs to join a live bidding room or place a proxy bid.
Goals:
- Enable users to quickly assess listing quality and provenance, understand auction timing, review AI QA results, and make informed bidding decisions via immediate bids or proxy bidding workflows.
Connected features:
- Search & Filter Functionality: Full-text search and rich facet filters to surface listings efficiently at scale.
- Notifications & Alerts: Transactional emails/SMS (outbid, auction starting, inspection scheduled) and in-app notifications with user-preference management.
- Caching & Performance: CDN, edge caching, and DB optimization strategies to keep UI snappy in a high-concurrency environment.
UI elements and how they look:
- Media Gallery: Responsive grid/carousel with high-res images, angle tags (e.g., Front, Rear, Interior), and video support when present.
- Specs Panel: Rich metadata including a VIN-like identifier, provenance notes, and extensible fields supplied by AI/augmented data enrichment.
- AI QA Report: Structured JSON-driven panel showing key findings, failures vs warnings, tags, confidence scores, and clickable evidence thumbnails.
- Auction Summary: Schedule (batches), reserve status, current highest bid, time remaining, and deposit/requirement indicators.
- Bid Widget: Immediate bid input, proxy bid setup with max amount, confirm modal, visible outbid thresholds, and visible deposit requirement.
- Bid History: Chronological, anonymized buyer IDs, bid amounts, timestamps, and status (accepted/outbid).
- Watchlist & Notification toggles: User can watch a listing and configure notification preferences at listing level.
- Live CTA: Primary “Join Live Bidding” action and a secondary “Set Proxy Bid” action with a guided modal.
