## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Framework: Next.js with App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS.
- State management: React useState/useEffect, React Context for global UI state (e.g., user preferences, watchlist).
- Data fetching: fetch API wrappers with null-safety; use data ?? [] for array results; guard against non-arrays: Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- Accessibility: aria-labels, keyboard navigation, focus indicators.
- Real-time: Supabase Realtime or WebSockets for Live Auction Room updates; ensure proper security with RLS and tokenized channels.
- Routing: /listings/[id] with nested routes for /live (Live Auction Room) and /auction (detail view); server components where appropriate, client components for interactive widgets.
- Validation: input validation for bid amounts, proxy max, and required media uploads (15–25 photos with angle validation).
- Security: authentication with session tokens, authorization checks for bidding actions, and server-side validation of bids.
- Performance: implement CDN caching hints, edge caching for listing detail, and optimized queries with indexed fields (e.g., id, batch_id, reserve_status).

### Backend
- API Routes / Endpoints (Next.js API Routes or Edge Functions)
  - GET /api/listings/:id
  - GET /api/listings/:id/bids
  - POST /api/listings/:id/bids (placeBid)
  - POST /api/listings/:id/proxy-bids (setupProxyBid)
  - POST /api/listings/:id/join-live (joinLiveAuction)
  - GET /api/listings/:id/ai-qa (aiQaReport)
  - GET /api/listings/:id/media
  - GET /api/search (full-text search)
  - POST /api/watchlist (toggleWatchlist)
  - GET /api/notifications/prefs
  - POST /api/notifications/prefs (updatePrefs)
- Database Tables (Postgres via Supabase)
  - listings(id, title, description, specs_json, vin_like_id, provenance, batch_id, auction_schedule_id, media_json, ai_qa_json, created_at, updated_at, ...)
  - bids(id, listing_id, user_id, amount, created_at, is_proxy, proxy_max, status)
  - auction_batches(id, start_time, end_time, status, reserve, current_highest_bid)
  - ai_qa_reports(id, listing_id, structured_json, confidence, flags_json, evidence_images_json)
  - media(id, listing_id, type, url, angle_tag, position)
  - users(id, name, email, phone, verified, deposits)
  - watchlists(id, user_id, listing_id, created_at, prefs_json)
  - notifications(user_id, listing_id, type, status, sent_at, payload_json)
  - audit_logs or events table for lifecycle tracking
- Functions & Logic
  - Concurrency-safe bidding with optimistic UI and server-side race condition protections
  - Proxy bidding engine logic with max bid enforcement, guard against sniping, and auction extension rules
  - AI QA data enrichment pipeline interface (provider-agnostic)
  - Integration adapters for email/SMS (webhooks, idempotent)
- Caching & Performance
  - Edge caching hints for listing detail endpoints
  - Supabase RLS permissions to constrain data per user
  - DB indices on listing_id, batch_id, created_at for bids and events

### Integration
- Provider-agnostic AI Vision integration
  - Define an AIProvider interface with methods: analyzeImages(images): AIQAResult[]
  - Pluggable adapters for: general vision API, specialist provider, and local rules-based checks
  - Output: structured JSON with fields: hard_fail, warnings, tags, confidence, evidence_images
- External enrichment APIs
  - Data fetchers for inspection history, provenance, VIN-like enrichment, and legal checks
  - Caching strategy for enrichment results with invalidation on listing updates
- Communication Providers
  - Email provider (Transactional templates with placeholders)
  - SMS provider (Transactional messages)
  - In-app notification service with per-user preferences
- Real-time Stack
  - Supabase Realtime channels per listing for bids, status updates
  - WebSocket fallback for environments without Realtime
- Payments
  - Stripe integration for deposits, payments, and recurring subscriptions
  - Webhooks with idempotency keys, auditable event handling

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on Listing Detail page (/listings/:id)
   - Page loads listing data, media gallery, specs, AI QA, auction schedule, and current bid info.
   - Users can scroll sections, view AI QA highlights, and read provenance.
2. User uses Search & Filters to surface listings
   - Full-text search with filters; results feed into listing detail page navigation.
3. User interacts with BidWidget
   - Enter amount, choose to place immediate bid or set a proxy bid with max amount.
   - Validate minimum increments, user deposit sufficiency, and reserve rules.
   - Confirm bid via modal; on success, UI updates with new highest bid.
4. User joins Live Auction Room
   - Click Join Live Bidding to load LiveAuctionRoom with real-time bids and timer.
   - See live bids, chat announcements, and quick-bid options.
5. Notifications
   - If user is outbid or auction is starting or inspection scheduled, trigger transactional emails/SMS and in-app notifications per preferences.
6. Watchlist & Preferences
   - User toggles watchlist; can configure per-listing notification preferences.
7. Caching & Performance
   - Listing detail uses edge caching; repeated visits serve from cache while validating freshness.
8. Admin/Ops flow (RBAC integration)
   - Admins can review AI QA results, verify provenance, monitor auctions, and manage disputes.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models: Detailed schema definitions (see below)
- API Endpoints: Routes and methods (see above)
- Security: JWT/session-based authentication, Supabase RLS, per-listing authorization checks
- Validation: Strong server-side validation for all inputs; use type guards; avoid undefined/null in array operations

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Listing Detail page renders with media gallery, specs, AI QA, auction schedule, bid history, and CTAs; all data loaded with null-safety: items = data ?? [], Array.isArray checks, and useState([]) defaults for arrays.
- [ ] Bid flow: user can place immediate bids or configure proxy bids; server ensures concurrency-safe bidding; no race conditions; appropriate UI feedback on success/failure.
- [ ] Live Auction Room: real-time updates flow with Supabase Realtime/WebSocket; timer, bids, and chat updates propagate accurately to participants.
- [ ] Notifications: transactional emails/SMS dispatched with idempotent webhooks; in-app notifications respect user preferences.
- [ ] Caching: listing detail data served from edge/CDN with proper stale-while-revalidate strategy; backend queries optimized with indexing.
- [ ] AI QA: AI QA reports are pluggable; provider-agnostic adapters implemented; structured results rendered in UI with highlights and evidence.

